title: Prep Football Week 10 Roundup
text:
Prep Football Week 10 Roundup Published: October 25, 2015 Blackman defense brings down Coffee County's Boone Riddle / Murfreesboro Post 
Stewarts Creek: 
With its fourth win in its last five games, Stewarts Creek appears to have nailed down its first-ever playoff berth. More from Maurice Patton of the Murfreesboro Post. 
READ MORE 
Blackman: Blackman made Senior Night a memorable one on Friday by rolling past Coffee County 42-20. The Blaze improved to 7-2 overall and 5-1 in region play, while the Red Raiders fell to 3-6 and 1-5. More from Matthew Sawyer of the Murfreesboro Post. 
READ MORE 
Eagleville:Eagleville struggled to stop the soon-to-be region champion at Forrest doubled the yardage of the in a 49-13 victory. More from Jake Bolden of the Murfreesboro Post.
